1. Setup and Required Secrets
- COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN: Create a fine-grained Personal Access Token with "GitHub Copilot -> Read" permission. Purpose: authenticates Copilot SDK for agentic tasks that modify repository contents using the SDK.
- WORKFLOW_TOKEN: Create a classic Personal Access Token with the "workflow" scope. Purpose: allows workflows (init.yml) to update files under .github/workflows/ (GITHUB_TOKEN cannot modify workflow files).
- Add secrets via Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret.

2. Repository and Actions Settings
- GitHub Actions must be allowed (Settings → Actions → General).
- Workflow permissions must be set to Read and write permissions for the repository actions to operate fully.
- Allow GitHub Actions to create pull requests (checkbox in Actions settings).
- Enable GitHub Discussions for the discussions bot (Settings → General → Features).
- Optional branch protection recommendations: require PR review and require status checks (use test workflow).

3. Workflow Pipeline and Execution
- Canonical pipeline: MISSION.md -> supervisor -> dispatch workflows -> Issue -> Code -> Test -> PR -> Merge.
- Supervisor acts as an LLM orchestrator; workflows use Copilot SDK to transform source, create tests, and open PRs.
- agentic-lib provides init and maintenance workflows; init.yml updates the agentic infra and can be invoked manually via npx @xn-intenton-z2a/agentic-lib@latest init.

4. agentic-lib.toml: Keys, Values and Profiles
- [schedule].supervisor: off | weekly | daily | hourly | continuous (example: continuous in local config; recommended default: daily).
- [paths]: mission, source, tests, features, library, docs, readme, dependencies, contributing, library-sources — use these to point workflows to repo layout.
- [execution].test: Command run by supervisor to validate code changes (example: npm ci && npm test).
- [limits]: max-feature-issues, max-maintenance-issues, max-attempts-per-branch, max-attempts-per-issue, features-limit, library-limit — numeric controls for agenting behavior.
- [tuning].model: Select model string: gpt-5-mini | claude-sonnet-4 | gpt-4.1. Set reasoning-effort: low | medium | high | none. Other tuning: infinite-sessions boolean, transformation-budget (max change cycles), max-source-chars, etc.
- Profiles: profiles.min, profiles.recommended, profiles.max. Each profile predefines reasoning-effort, infinite-sessions, transformation-budget, max-source-files, max-test-chars, max-issues, stale-days, max-summary-chars, max-discussion-comments, max-feature-issues, max-maintenance-issues, max-attempts-per-branch, max-attempts-per-issue, features-limit, library-limit.

